GEO:39.161697;-86.5309
SUMMARY:Saturday Crafternoons at the Wylie House Museum
DESCRIPTION:Theophilus Wylie and his family regularly pressed flowers and
  sent the specimens to one another as keepsakes. Records of this exist in
  the letters - many reference Anton Wylie and his father Hermann Boisen s
 ending leaves and flowers while Hermann was away on trips.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Theophilus Wylie and his family regular
 ly pressed flowers and sent the specimens to one another as keepsakes. Re
 cords of this exist in the letters - many reference Anton Wylie and his f
 ather Hermann Boisen sending leaves and flowers while Hermann was away on
  trips.&#160\;</p>
